data.name: Parkinsons
data.description: Parkinson's disease is a neurodegenerative disorder affecting movement. It is characterized by tremors, bradykinesia, rigidity, and postural instability. The condition results from the loss of dopamine-producing cells in the brain. Symptoms also include changes in speech and writing, as well as non-motor issues like cognitive impairment and depression. While the exact cause is unknown, both genetic and environmental factors are believed to play a role. Treatment involves medication, physical therapy, and in some cases, deep brain stimulation. Although there is currently no cure, early detection and management can significantly improve quality of life for individuals with Parkinson's.
